# Test logical plan for global aggregate without BY clause
query 'CALL rql::logical("from users aggregate { count(id) }")'
---
> +-------+---------+----------+-------------+-------------------------+
> |  idx  |  depth  |  parent  |    kind     |         detail          |
> +-------+---------+----------+-------------+-------------------------+
> |   0   |    0    |   none   |  TableScan  |     default::users      |
> |   1   |    0    |   none   |  Aggregate  |  by=[] map=[count(id)]  |
> +-------+---------+----------+-------------+-------------------------+
>

# Test logical plan for global aggregate with empty BY clause
query 'CALL rql::logical("from users aggregate { total: count(id), sum: sum(amount) } by {}")'
---
> +-------+---------+----------+-------------+------------------------------------------------------+
> |  idx  |  depth  |  parent  |    kind     |                        detail                        |
> +-------+---------+----------+-------------+------------------------------------------------------+
> |   0   |    0    |   none   |  TableScan  |                    default::users                    |
> |   1   |    0    |   none   |  Aggregate  |  by=[] map=[count(id) as total, sum(amount) as sum]  |
> +-------+---------+----------+-------------+------------------------------------------------------+
>

